Hi if Newsbreak App is selected (only option) as the ad placement will it give me desktop clicks too?

Hi! If you select the NewsBreak App as your ad placement, it will primarily target mobile users within the app. For desktop clicks, you would need to consider additional placements that include desktop inventory. Let me know if you have any other questions!
I need to exclude desktop users completely

To exclude desktop users completely, you can set your targeting preferences to focus solely on mobile devices. When setting up your campaign, make sure to select only mobile device types in the targeting options. This way, your ads will be shown exclusively to mobile users. If you need further assistance with this setup, feel free to ask!
is there a way to disable duplicate clicks from users

To manage duplicate clicks, you can implement unique transaction IDs or user identifiers in your tracking setup. This helps in identifying and filtering out duplicate conversions. Additionally, ensure that your postback setup is correctly configured to pass these unique identifiers. If you need more detailed guidance on setting this up, let me know!
no i want to show an ad to a person that has never clicked on it before

To target users who have never clicked on your ad before, you can use exclusion targeting. In the ad setup, you can exclude audiences based on their previous actions, such as excluding users who have already clicked on your ad. This will help ensure that your ads are shown to new users only. If you need more help with setting this up, feel free to ask!
I created an audience of people that clicked on my ad. These people I want to exclude from seeing my ad. do new people that click get automatically inserted in this audience?

Yes, if you've set up an audience based on ad engagement, such as clicks, new users who click on your ad will automatically be added to this audience. This allows you to continuously update and exclude these users from seeing your ad again. Make sure your audience settings are configured to dynamically include new engagements for this to work effectively.
when trying to create a new event i get this error message. tried it 5 times already: Invalid operation. Please reach out to your account manager if problem persists.

It sounds like you're encountering an issue with creating a new event. This error message suggests that there might be a problem with your account settings or permissions. If you have an Account Manager, I recommend reaching out to them for assistance. If not, you can contact our support team at adsupport@newsbreak.com for help. They should be able to assist you in resolving this issue.
